=Description=

"MyZone is a peer to peer social networking application and is part of a research project conducted under the supervision of Dr. Richard Han, Dr. Shivakant Mishra and Dr. Eric Keller at the computer science department of the University of Colorado at Boulder with the goal of achieving free and safe internet.

MyZone provides an online social network where users are hosting their own profiles on their own computers without the need of a publicly accessible server. This means unlike other social networking sites, the user privacy is always preserved as their profile information is only visible to and accessible by their friends on the social network. This approach is different from traditional social networking sites like Facebook, where user data is being hosted on centralized servers and can be used for targeted advertisement which may result in violation of user privacy.

MyZone in its complete form is also resilient to service blocking and censorship imposed by government entities. In other words, MyZone gurantees free speech for all of its users anywhere in the world."
(http://joinmyzone.com/about.html)

